	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98112511131396>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>RE: how to build 1hs</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Feb 2nd 2:48 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=20015><span id=Scholar>Muttonchopps</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>40 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.47]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>There is only one condition that you have to meet in order to raise combat skills.&nbsp;&nbsp;You have to make sure that the monster you are fighting is /con at least blue to you.<br><br>This is probably the best way to increase your attack, defense, and weapon skills:<br><br>1.  Buff yourself up, i.e. Skin like X, X-Coat, Spirit of Wolf (try to get your AC as high as possible, the more armor class you have the less damage you take when you get hit).<br><br>2.  Find a monster that cons blue to you.<br><br>3.  Cast a Damage shield on yourself. <br><br>4.  Pull the monster by casting snare or ensnare on it.<br><br>5.  Let him beat you up while you are fighting it. (do not cast damage spells on the monster, save your mana for healing).<br><br>6.  If you are dying you can run a ways away and heal yourself, then get back into the fight.<br><br>7.  At a certain point the monster will try to run away from you.  If it is ensared it will turn away as if it were gunna run, but will be stuck in place.<br><br>8.  Use this opportunity to hack away at him with your weapon.  Put yourself on auto-attack and you can go get a coke or use the rest room.<br><br>9.  Reapply snare or ensnare when it breaks.<br><br>Note:  Your Defense will go up when the monster is swinging at you.  Your Attack will go up any time you damage the monster (attack will go up when the monster hurts himself on your damage shield).  Your weapon skills will go up when you are swinging at the monster.</p>&nbsp;<br>Muttonchopps Ingells<br>54th level Wanderer<br>&lt;Lost Legacy&gt;<br>Test Server</td></td></tr>
	     <tr><td colspan=2 align=right class=mform id=fs8>1 Replies</td></tr>
