	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=20015><span id=Scholar>Muttonchopps</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>40 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.47]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>"At level 24 this strategy won't work due to the fact that mobs hit relatively hard" - Anonymous <br><br>You don't have a clue my friend. The damage that mobs do to you is directly related to your armor class. The more you do this the higher your AC increases... the less damage you take per hit... the longer you can stick in a fight. Sure, you will get beat up fast.. but with your damage shield + your mana reserved for healing you can take out just about any blue mob no matter what level you are. <br><br>I was level 52 when I first used this tactic. At that time the Spirocs in Timourous Deep were still blue to me (level 36 to 42 I think). Spirocs are some hard hitting mofos (probably more significant damage than any monsters at level 24 that you think hit "relatively hard"). At about average 90 points per hit, I could only take a dozen or so hits before I had to run away to heal up. 12 hits x 29 points of damage(shield of Thorns + thorn coat)= 288 points of self inflicted damage on the mob. You can reasonably repeat this scenario for however many times it takes until the monster turns tail to run away. <br><br>So you see, level 24 definitely isn't the cap for using this tactic. You can potentially use this tactic to catch up with your skills no matter what level you are at. Be creative, don't say that something can't be done because it looks hard.<br></p>&nbsp;<br>Muttonchopps Ingells<br>54th level Wanderer<br>&lt;Lost Legacy&gt;<br>Test Server</td></td></tr>
